    "India ranks 3rd globally in greenhouse gas emissions, accounting for ~6.6% of world CO2e",
    "Power generation (coal) is the single largest sector at 1.23 billion tonnes CO2e — nearly a third of India's total",
    "The top 10 coal power plants alone emit 229 Mt CO2e — equivalent to the entire emissions of many countries",
    "NTPC Ltd operates 5 of India's 10 most polluting power plants (Vindhyachal, Rihand, Talcher, Korba, Sipat)",
    "Agriculture is the 2nd largest sector: cattle (enteric fermentation + manure) emits 328 Mt CO2e, and rice cultivation adds 115 Mt",
    "India's rice paddies emit more CO2e than its entire transportation sector's aviation and shipping combined",
    "Steel and cement together account for 341 Mt CO2e — 83% of manufacturing emissions",
    "Road transport dominates transportation at 80% (176 Mt), while railways show zero direct emissions",
    "Coal mining (66 Mt) and oil refining (67 Mt) are nearly equal contributors in fossil fuel operations",
    "Waste sector is relatively small at 14 Mt, but solid waste disposal and wastewater are growing concerns"
